The paper focuses on the resource requirements of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) on mobile devices, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the potential deployment of deep learning applications on mobile devices, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes a modeling tool to estimate the resource requirements of CNNs on mobile devices, which could fall under computer architecture (cs.AR).
